750
00:58:06,526 --> 00:58:08,403
That's not normal, is it?

751
00:58:08,487 --> 00:58:10,572
Listen, when it comes to the brain,
nothing is normal,

752
00:58:10,697 --> 00:58:12,824
because no two brain 
injuries are the same.

753
00:58:12,908 --> 00:58:15,744
Paige seems perfectly herself again.

754
00:58:15,869 --> 00:58:17,412
It's wonderful.

755
00:58:17,871 --> 00:58:20,248
Mrs. Thornton, could I just talk to 
Paige alone for a moment, please?

756
00:58:22,167 --> 00:58:24,920
It's okay, Mom. I'm... I'm good.

757
00:58:27,839 --> 00:58:29,216
All right.

758
00:58:30,884 --> 00:58:32,094
Thanks.

759
00:58:39,434 --> 00:58:42,354
Paige, do you want to 
regain your memory?

760
00:58:42,437 --> 00:58:43,605
Yes.

761
00:58:43,689 --> 00:58:46,191
Because some patients fear
that when their memory comes back,

762
00:58:46,274 --> 00:58:49,111
so will the memory of the trauma,
but mercifully that's rarely the case.

763
00:58:49,194 --> 00:58:51,363
Oh, no, that's not it. I'm... I'm...

764
00:58:51,446 --> 00:58:53,407
I'm not afraid of the accident.

765
00:58:54,199 --> 00:58:55,701
So, what are you afraid of?

766
00:58:59,538 --> 00:59:02,874
I guess I just... I don't know. It's...

767
00:59:04,292 --> 00:59:07,045
I mean, what if I don't 
like the life that I had?

768
00:59:07,129 --> 00:59:08,714
Or what if I like it too much?

769
00:59:08,797 --> 00:59:10,048
I...

770
00:59:10,132 --> 00:59:12,050
I just don't know.

771
00:59:12,467 --> 00:59:16,471
I only did one psych rotation,
so this may be terrible advice.

772
00:59:17,389 --> 00:59:20,559
But I think you have 
to try and fill the holes.

773
00:59:21,435 --> 00:59:23,812
You can still decide 
you want a different life,

774
00:59:23,895 --> 00:59:27,399
but if you don't at least
open yourself up to remembering,

775
00:59:27,482 --> 00:59:31,069
I'm afraid you're gonna live 
in fear of your own past.

776
00:59:33,739 --> 00:59:35,490
Hey. I'm here.

777
00:59:37,993 --> 00:59:39,411
These guys are?

778
00:59:39,494 --> 00:59:42,247
Knife Skillz, With a Z.

779
00:59:42,330 --> 00:59:43,623
Right.

780
00:59:44,499 --> 00:59:47,836
Okay, Mikey, sounds amazing.
Let's just go for it.

781
00:59:49,004 --> 00:59:50,505
I am going for it.

782
00:59:50,589 --> 00:59:52,007
The bass line is one note.

783
00:59:52,174 --> 00:59:54,468
- Just one note.
- Okay, cool.

784
00:59:54,968 --> 00:59:56,344
Take two.

785
01:00:01,183 --> 01:00:02,934
You look different.

786
01:00:03,018 --> 01:00:06,021
Yeah. Going for a Kanye kind of thing.

787
01:00:06,146 --> 01:00:09,357
I'm gonna say more Michael Bublé,
but, whatever, it's still good.

788
01:00:12,652 --> 01:00:15,864
So... I'm gonna be in 
and out for a while.

789
01:00:19,618 --> 01:00:21,036
Sounds really good, Mikey.

790
01:00:21,119 --> 01:00:24,873
Let's just take it from the top
or the middle or wherever.

791
01:00:26,458 --> 01:00:29,878
You know what? People come 
here to work with you, okay?

792
01:00:30,003 --> 01:00:32,881
I mean, I'm doing my best,
but you gotta be here.

793
01:00:33,006 --> 01:00:34,341
I know.

794
01:00:34,716 --> 01:00:37,803
But if Paige is in Lake 
Forest with her family,

795
01:00:38,011 --> 01:00:39,554
that's where I gotta be.

796
01:00:39,638 --> 01:00:42,390
I gotta make my wife
fall in love with me again.

797
01:00:53,735 --> 01:00:55,821
- You found each other.
