805
01:01:13,713 --> 01:01:16,174
No, honey, it's like a good dizzy. It's like...

806
01:01:16,258 --> 01:01:19,427
It's like panic or excitement.

807
01:01:21,429 --> 01:01:24,349
Well, panic and excitement are different.

808
01:01:24,432 --> 01:01:27,269
- Honey, there's gonna be 400 people there.
- Right.

809
01:01:27,853 --> 01:01:30,856
Hey, do you also have
a little tingling in your fingers?

810
01:01:30,939 --> 01:01:33,567
Yeah. Is that bad?

811
01:01:33,775 --> 01:01:36,027
Do you listen to Radiohead?

812
01:01:36,111 --> 01:01:39,739
Thom Yorke,
he talks about dizzy spells all the time.

813
01:01:40,490 --> 01:01:42,242
He says when his fingers tingle,

814
01:01:42,325 --> 01:01:45,829
that's how he knows
that he's creating something genius.

815
01:01:45,954 --> 01:01:49,499
And then he gets so amped up 
playing that he almost passes out.

816
01:01:49,624 --> 01:01:53,169
Ryan, it sounds to me like 
you're on the verge of genius.

817
01:01:53,295 --> 01:01:55,380
- That's cool, man.
- Cheers.

818
01:01:55,463 --> 01:01:57,841
Ryan, I have someone 
I want you to meet.

819
01:01:57,966 --> 01:02:00,844
- Mom, you listen to Radiohead?
- Yeah. Why wouldn't I?

820
01:02:00,969 --> 01:02:02,971
So, is that true?

821
01:02:11,605 --> 01:02:12,647
Paige?

822
01:02:13,940 --> 01:02:15,317
Hey, Leo.

823
01:02:18,987 --> 01:02:20,906
- What?
- Your hair.

824
01:02:20,989 --> 01:02:22,490
It looks so different.

825
01:02:23,450 --> 01:02:25,827
- You look beautiful.
- Thank you.

826
01:02:26,494 --> 01:02:28,830
Okay, look, so I've been 
thinking about something.

827
01:02:28,955 --> 01:02:31,625
- Okay.
- What's your favorite book?

828
01:02:32,959 --> 01:02:36,755
- It's probably not what you remember.
- That's fine. That's not the point.

829
01:02:36,838 --> 01:02:39,299
Okay. The Beach House by James Patterson.

830
01:02:39,382 --> 01:02:41,509
- No, really?
- Yeah.

831
01:02:41,635 --> 01:02:44,179
Okay. The Beach House.

832
01:02:45,138 --> 01:02:48,099
Okay, if it was great, you probably 
loaned it to somebody, right?

833
01:02:48,183 --> 01:02:50,226
Yeah. Gwen, I think.

834
01:02:50,352 --> 01:02:52,979
Okay, and you probably said to yourself,

835
01:02:53,063 --> 01:02:55,482
God, I wish I was the person
that hadn't read it,

836
01:02:55,565 --> 01:02:57,984
"so that I could experience it all over again."

837
01:02:58,068 --> 01:02:59,986
Yeah, I guess so.

838
01:03:00,070 --> 01:03:02,030
That's how I think we should look at this.

839
01:03:04,199 --> 01:03:05,408
What?

840
01:03:06,701 --> 01:03:09,371
You can't remember how we met.

841
01:03:09,746 --> 01:03:12,040
And you can't remember 
how we fell in love.

842
01:03:12,165 --> 01:03:14,793
And in a way, yeah, that sucks.

843
01:03:14,876 --> 01:03:19,047
But it was the greatest time of my life.

844
01:03:20,423 --> 01:03:23,593
I just thought how cool it would be
to get to experience it all over again.

845
01:03:24,886 --> 01:03:27,180
Like reading your favorite book
for the first time.

846
01:03:27,263 --> 01:03:29,057
- Exactly.
- Got you.

847
01:03:29,516 --> 01:03:31,726
Which is why I want to 
ask you out on a date.

848
01:03:34,229 --> 01:03:35,605
A date?

849
01:03:35,730 --> 01:03:37,941
Like two people that are just 
meeting for the first time.

850
01:03:38,775 --> 01:03:40,193
Jeremy...

851
01:03:41,403 --> 01:03:42,988
Yeah, I'm sorry.

852
01:03:43,071 --> 01:03:47,784
Well, I don't know. I mean, you know,
we've got the wedding coming up.

853
01:03:47,909 --> 01:03:49,536
But if we go out before then,

854
01:03:49,619 --> 01:03:51,955
you might still be able
to take me as your date.

855
01:03:52,080 --> 01:03:56,126
I can't promise anything,
but I'll put in a good word for you.

856
01:03:57,794 --> 01:03:59,254
All right.

857
01:03:59,379 --> 01:04:00,797
- Yeah?
- A date.

858
01:04:11,057 --> 01:04:14,019
So, I have an idea, but it 
involves going into the city.

859
01:04:14,102 --> 01:04:16,855
- You okay with that?
- Yeah, that's fine.

860
01:04:16,938 --> 01:04:19,441
I just have to be back
by 10:00 in the morning.

861
01:04:19,566 --> 01:04:21,776
- Oh, my God.
- What?

862
01:04:21,943 --> 01:04:24,738
First date and you're already
inviting yourself to stay the night?

863
01:04:24,821 --> 01:04:26,948
I'm just a little scandalized is all.

864
01:04:27,073 --> 01:04:30,535
- No, I just meant...
- Don't worry. I'll have you back tonight.

865
01:04:30,618 --> 01:04:35,081
If you wanna stay the night, that's...
I mean, it's... If you want...

866
01:04:35,290 --> 01:04:38,293
You wanna just see how it goes? All right.

867
01:04:56,478 --> 01:04:58,313
Should we get out?

868
01:04:58,438 --> 01:05:00,315
We don't have to.

869
01:05:00,607 --> 01:05:02,233
Is this the part of the 
date where I find out

870
01:05:02,317 --> 01:05:05,361
you're not actually my husband
but some crazy stalker,

871
01:05:05,487 --> 01:05:07,530
and you're gonna strangle me
with my purse?

872
01:05:07,655 --> 01:05:12,285
No. This is the exact parking spot
where we first met.

873
01:05:15,288 --> 01:05:18,124
I'm gonna take you on
a little retrospective of us.

874
01:05:27,717 --> 01:05:29,511
That is so good.

875
01:05:29,969 --> 01:05:31,930
You ready for dessert?

876
01:05:32,013 --> 01:05:33,640
Dessert?

877
01:05:34,140 --> 01:05:37,227
- We just had waffles.
- This is dinner.

878
01:05:38,478 --> 01:05:40,980
These are dessert.

879
01:05:43,191 --> 01:05:45,985
Well, how do you know
what flavors they all are?

880
01:05:46,069 --> 01:05:49,781
It's like a chocolate Russian roulette.
It's part of the fun.

881
01:05:49,864 --> 01:05:52,867
We'd be surprised by the ones 
we liked and the ones we didn't.

882
01:05:52,992 --> 01:05:54,160
Okay.

883
01:05:56,246 --> 01:05:57,372
And...

884
01:05:58,706 --> 01:06:01,376
- You don't like it?
- I do not like that one.

885
01:06:01,501 --> 01:06:04,337
Here. Try this one. 
I think you'd like this one.

886
01:06:11,386 --> 01:06:13,429
- Told you.
- Okay.

887
01:06:15,348 --> 01:06:16,724
Your turn.

888
01:06:19,727 --> 01:06:21,896
Are we going shot for shot?

889
01:06:27,861 --> 01:06:30,029
Wait till you try their hot chocolate.

890
01:06:30,113 --> 01:06:32,157
We would come here 
whenever it snowed.

891
01:06:32,240 --> 01:06:34,242
Are you trying to make me diabetic
or just fat?

892
01:06:34,367 --> 01:06:35,702
No, I...

893
01:06:40,456 --> 01:06:43,209
You got a... It's still in your hair.

894
01:06:55,471 --> 01:06:59,267
So, we come down here at night
and look at the lake?

895
01:07:00,059 --> 01:07:02,312
That's not exactly what we do.

896
01:07:06,900 --> 01:07:08,818
I... I'm not...

897
01:07:09,652 --> 01:07:12,113
- I don't...
- No, no, it's not that.

898
01:07:12,238 --> 01:07:15,909
We said we'd go in once a month every
month, and we haven't done April yet.

899
01:07:16,993 --> 01:07:18,786
We started in July.

900
01:07:22,081 --> 01:07:24,375
Why? Why would we do that?

901
01:07:24,459 --> 01:07:28,338
We were at this spaghetti place, and 
we had this waiter and he said he did it.

902
01:07:28,463 --> 01:07:30,798
And he was, like, 80.
So we thought we could.

903
01:07:30,924 --> 01:07:32,342
Yeah.

904
01:07:32,467 --> 01:07:35,261
- Now, we said no wetsuits, but...
- You're serious.

905
01:07:35,345 --> 01:07:37,847
...for you, I guess I'll make an exception.

906
01:07:45,313 --> 01:07:47,607
All right. Turn around.

907
01:07:49,150 --> 01:07:50,652
Turn around.

908
01:08:01,329 --> 01:08:02,455
Okay.

909
01:08:03,873 --> 01:08:06,459
- Wait. No wetsuit?
- We said no wetsuits, right?

910
01:08:11,130 --> 01:08:12,173
Yeah.

911
01:08:16,344 --> 01:08:17,762
Oh, no.

912
01:08:17,845 --> 01:08:19,472
No,no.No,no!

913
01:08:33,319 --> 01:08:34,570
Come on.

914
01:08:45,748 --> 01:08:46,874
Thank you.

915
01:08:50,545 --> 01:08:53,673
- Heat, heat.
- My left eyelid's frozen shut.

916
01:08:59,554 --> 01:09:01,556
I can't feel my fingers.

917
01:09:04,017 --> 01:09:05,184
I can't feel them.

918
01:09:17,947 --> 01:09:20,158
I don't know what your 
Paige did on a first date,

919
01:09:20,241 --> 01:09:24,537
but with me, you're 
only getting to first base.

920
01:09:26,414 --> 01:09:27,623
Okay.

921
01:09:32,920 --> 01:09:36,591
I'm sorry. I can do better.
My... My lips are still numb.

922
01:09:39,927 --> 01:09:41,429
It's nice.

923
01:09:50,313 --> 01:09:52,106
Second base, tops.

924
01:09:53,566 --> 01:09:55,276
This is perfect.

925
01:10:16,506 --> 01:10:19,133
Thank you for coming 
out with me tonight.

926
01:10:19,258 --> 01:10:21,469
I had a really nice time.

927
01:10:25,139 --> 01:10:26,849
I've missed you.

928
01:10:27,642 --> 01:10:30,603
I miss our life together.
I miss being with you.

929
01:10:35,108 --> 01:10:36,526
I love you.

930
01:10:43,699 --> 01:10:47,286
I should probably get inside.

931
01:10:50,498 --> 01:10:53,334
Good night.

932
01:11:12,562 --> 01:11:13,896
Hey.

933
01:11:15,022 --> 01:11:17,859
Hey. I didn't know you 
were gonna be here.

934
01:11:18,526 --> 01:11:20,111
Were you out with Jeremy?

935
01:11:20,194 --> 01:11:21,446
No.

936
01:11:21,863 --> 01:11:23,614
I was with Leo.

937
01:11:25,074 --> 01:11:26,701
I like him.

938
01:11:29,370 --> 01:11:30,580
Yeah.

939
01:11:31,956 --> 01:11:33,458
Me, too.

940
01:11:35,251 --> 01:11:36,752
Are you okay?

941
01:11:41,966 --> 01:11:45,219
Paige, I've never seen you like this before.

942
01:11:45,303 --> 01:11:47,722
I mean, is this crying thing the new you?

943
01:11:47,805 --> 01:11:49,682
Because it's bizarre.

944
01:11:49,765 --> 01:11:53,394
I don't know. I don't know what's me.
I have a tattoo.

945
01:11:56,606 --> 01:11:58,816
And I'm a vegetarian, too.

946
01:12:00,568 --> 01:12:03,905
Look, it was just like it used to be.
It was better, actually.

947
01:12:04,739 --> 01:12:08,826
Everything that I fell in love with
about Paige is still there.

948
01:12:09,160 --> 01:12:13,748
You know, to you, I'm sure it seemed
like a confirmation of your love

949
01:12:13,831 --> 01:12:15,583
or your marriage, right?

950
01:12:15,666 --> 01:12:18,461
But to her, it probably seemed 
more like a really good first date.

951
01:12:18,586 --> 01:12:20,505
Exactly. Which is why
I think you've gotta wait

952
01:12:20,588 --> 01:12:22,131
the requisite three days before you call.

953
01:12:22,256 --> 01:12:25,927
