after a date with my own wife?

954
01:12:26,010 --> 01:12:28,554
At least. This is a unique case. Maybe longer.

955
01:12:28,638 --> 01:12:30,973
It can't be longer. I'm gonna see
her on Saturday at the wedding.

956
01:12:31,098 --> 01:12:32,892
I'm telling you, it was so obvious.

957
01:12:32,975 --> 01:12:35,937
Even with all this crazy shit going 
on around us, we still belong together.

958
01:12:36,020 --> 01:12:38,981
- Obvious to her or to you?
- To both of us.

959
01:12:40,525 --> 01:12:42,026
- Paige?
- Yeah?

960
01:12:42,109 --> 01:12:45,071
We have to start writing out
those place cards after we eat.

961
01:12:45,154 --> 01:12:46,489
Yes.

962
01:12:47,156 --> 01:12:49,116
Before you start on that,

963
01:12:50,451 --> 01:12:53,788
I have a little surprise for you, Paige.

964
01:12:55,665 --> 01:12:57,416
You know Ray Porter, right?

965
01:12:57,500 --> 01:13:00,169
He taught constitutional 
law at Northwestern.

966
01:13:00,294 --> 01:13:04,298
He and I were on law review together.
We've known each other 1,000 years.

967
01:13:05,299 --> 01:13:07,260
He is the dean of the law school now.

968
01:13:07,343 --> 01:13:10,221
- Okay.
- And they're gonna let you back in.

969
01:13:10,304 --> 01:13:11,889
What?

970
01:13:11,973 --> 01:13:13,474
Well...

971
01:13:14,141 --> 01:13:16,227
I didn't even apply.

972
01:13:16,310 --> 01:13:17,979
I took care of it.

973
01:13:20,022 --> 01:13:23,192
This is crazy.

974
01:13:25,236 --> 01:13:28,489
I feel like I'm getting a 
free do-over in life.

975
01:15:00,164 --> 01:15:01,957
You look like you could use a drink.

976
01:15:03,250 --> 01:15:04,877
I've already had several.

977
01:15:04,960 --> 01:15:07,088
But you haven't had this.

978
01:15:09,340 --> 01:15:10,758
All right.

979
01:15:12,134 --> 01:15:14,762
I'm glad we're having a moment alone.

980
01:15:14,845 --> 01:15:18,349
I haven't gotten a chance
to really talk to you, Leo.

981
01:15:18,516 --> 01:15:19,809
Yeah.

982
01:15:19,934 --> 01:15:21,602
Yeah, cool.

983
01:15:22,603 --> 01:15:24,271
Congratulations.

984
01:15:28,776 --> 01:15:31,112
- That's nice.
- Yes, it is.

985
01:15:33,781 --> 01:15:35,741
I've been thinking.

986
01:15:35,825 --> 01:15:40,996
And I think that it's probably time
to let us take it from here.

987
01:15:41,122 --> 01:15:42,373
Take what?

988
01:15:43,040 --> 01:15:44,792
Things with Paige.

989
01:15:45,960 --> 01:15:48,170
Look, I know she didn't have
health insurance because

990
01:15:48,295 --> 01:15:51,298
you chose to live in a certain way,

991
01:15:52,466 --> 01:15:54,301
and I know you must 
be drowning in debt.

992
01:15:55,386 --> 01:15:57,972
But I also know a way out of this.

993
01:15:58,681 --> 01:16:00,182
What's that?

994
01:16:01,308 --> 01:16:02,810
Divorce her.

995
01:16:04,061 --> 01:16:06,313
The bills have only just begun, Leo.

996
01:16:08,649 --> 01:16:12,445
Mr. Thornton, I don't think this is 
the time or the place to discuss this.

997
01:16:12,528 --> 01:16:15,531
Fine. If you don't care
about losing your business,

998
01:16:15,656 --> 01:16:19,577
which, clearly, you don't, 
what about Paige?

999
01:16:19,660 --> 01:16:22,621
What about doing what is
obviously the right thing for her?

1000
01:16:22,705 --> 01:16:24,999
- And you know what's right for her?
- As a matter of fact, I do.

1001
01:16:25,666 --> 01:16:28,461
- You're such a hypocrite.
- What did you say?

1002
01:16:28,544 --> 01:16:31,505
If you're such a family 
man, how come I...

1003
01:16:31,589 --> 01:16:35,009
I never once saw you come and try
to put things back together with Paige?

1004
01:16:39,847 --> 01:16:41,682
You're such a coward.

1005
01:16:57,865 --> 01:17:00,034
Hey, can I introduce you around a little bit?

1006
01:17:00,743 --> 01:17:04,205
- Can't feel good to be the odd man out.
- I'm not the odd man out.

1007
01:17:04,455 --> 01:17:07,958
All right. If you say so. You just seem
a little creepy over here all by yourself.

1008
01:17:08,042 --> 01:17:10,044
I'm just waiting for Paige, man.

1009
01:17:10,127 --> 01:17:12,296
All right, well, best of luck with that.

1010
01:17:12,379 --> 01:17:13,881
You like this, right?

1011
01:17:15,382 --> 01:17:18,093
- I'm sorry, like what?
- Paige leaves you behind.

1012
01:17:18,219 --> 01:17:21,889
She goes and has this life without you,
with some guy that no one gets.

1013
01:17:21,972 --> 01:17:23,557
And now you get to 
see her reject all that.

1014
01:17:24,391 --> 01:17:26,769
I mean, I like it a little bit.

1015
01:17:26,936 --> 01:17:28,270
Yeah?

1016
01:17:28,395 --> 01:17:30,356
Well, let me tell you what I like.

1017
01:17:30,439 --> 01:17:33,150
I like the fact that Paige told me
everything about you, Jeremy.

1018
01:17:34,109 --> 01:17:35,236
Okay.

1019
01:17:35,319 --> 01:17:38,447
She told me that when she was with you,

1020
01:17:39,657 --> 01:17:43,327
she would wake up at night in a panic,
thinking, "Is this all there is?"

1021
01:17:45,287 --> 01:17:47,665
She told you everything, huh?

1022
01:17:47,832 --> 01:17:50,334
Did she tell you that she threw 
herself at me the other day?

1023
01:17:50,417 --> 01:17:52,294
Did she tell you that?

1024
01:17:52,419 --> 01:17:56,090
Or did she stop telling you everything
when she forgot who the hell you were?

1025
01:17:58,467 --> 01:18:00,427
Look, I get why you're being such a dick.

1026
01:18:01,095 --> 01:18:03,931
You obviously love her, and you 
think you're gonna get her back.

1027
01:18:04,765 --> 01:18:07,268
But the thing is, she outgrew you.

1028
01:18:07,810 --> 01:18:10,104
What makes you think
that won't happen again?

1029
01:18:10,646 --> 01:18:12,606
Thank you for that advice.

1030
01:18:12,690 --> 01:18:15,276
I will mull it over while I'm 
in bed with your wife.

1031
01:18:16,986 --> 01:18:18,195
Leo!

1032
01:18:30,332 --> 01:18:32,585
- Paige, wait!
- What the hell were you thinking?

1033
01:18:32,668 --> 01:18:36,839
I don't know. That's a really good question,
because I have been driving myself insane,

1034
01:18:36,964 --> 01:18:39,216
making a complete ass of myself!

1035
01:18:39,300 --> 01:18:42,177
Literally trying everything possible
to try to save what we have.

1036
01:18:42,303 --> 01:18:44,305
And you've been
throwing yourself at Jeremy.

1037
01:18:45,139 --> 01:18:47,516
- That's not fair.
- It's not fair?

1038
01:18:49,643 --> 01:18:51,979
I see the way you look at him.

1039
01:18:53,814 --> 01:18:55,065
I know,

1040
01:18:56,317 --> 01:18:59,153
because you used to 
look at me that way.

1041
01:19:02,031 --> 01:19:04,950
- Leo, I...
- No, I think we need to start being realistic.

1042
01:19:05,034 --> 01:19:06,827
Your memory's not coming back.

1043
01:19:07,912 --> 01:19:10,581
The fact is that I'm still just a stranger.

1044
01:19:12,499 --> 01:19:14,668
I'm not trying to hurt you.

1045
01:19:16,921 --> 01:19:18,505
But I'm just...

1046
01:19:21,926 --> 01:19:24,845
I'm so tired of disappointing you.

1047
01:19:26,889 --> 01:19:28,182
I know.

1048
01:19:29,892 --> 01:19:31,518
I'm so sorry.

1049
01:19:35,064 --> 01:19:37,441
I'll apologize to Gwen and Ryan.

1050
01:19:37,524 --> 01:19:40,277
Oh, God, no, it's fine.

1051
01:19:41,737 --> 01:19:45,574
Wedding disasters have a way
of turning into great stories.

1052
01:19:47,368 --> 01:19:48,869
Eventually.

1053
01:19:56,085 --> 01:20:00,547
How do you look at the girl you love
and tell yourself it's time to walk away?

1054
01:20:10,432 --> 01:20:11,475
Leo?

1055
01:20:16,105 --> 01:20:19,733
I hope one day I can love
the way that you love me.

1056
01:20:23,070 --> 01:20:25,114
You figured it out once.

1057
01:20:26,573 --> 01:20:28,575
You'll do it again.

1058
01:21:44,151 --> 01:21:45,527
Shit.

1059
01:21:45,861 --> 01:21:47,988
You're here, not there.

1060
01:21:48,655 --> 01:21:50,324
Are you okay?

1061
01:21:50,407 --> 01:21:51,700
I'm done.

1062
01:21:52,159 --> 01:21:54,495
It's over. I give up.

1063
01:21:55,162 --> 01:21:56,830
No, you never give up, Leo.

1064
01:21:56,914 --> 01:22:00,751
No, if we were meant to be 
together, we would be together.

1065
01:22:03,378 --> 01:22:06,799
I was just thinking about the first time
that we went to that Greek restaurant

1066
01:22:06,882 --> 01:22:08,383
on the corner.

1067
01:22:08,509 --> 01:22:11,929
There was this big banner saying
"Now Serving Soup,"

1068
01:22:12,846 --> 01:22:18,435
and I just started to go on and on
about all the obstacles

1069
01:22:18,519 --> 01:22:20,145
that the owner must have overcome

1070
01:22:20,229 --> 01:22:22,689
to achieve his lifelong 
dream of serving soup.

1071
01:22:24,566 --> 01:22:27,027
And then... And when I was finished...

1072
01:22:28,195 --> 01:22:32,074
She didn't say anything for
a few seconds and she just...

1073
01:22:34,243 --> 01:22:36,453
She just sort of exhaled it.

1074
01:22:38,247 --> 01:22:40,374
It was almost to herself.

1075
01:22:41,917 --> 01:22:43,460
"I love you."

1076
01:22:45,129 --> 01:22:47,214
And it just hung there.

1077
01:22:48,382 --> 01:22:52,261
It was the first time she had said it,
and I didn't even wanna respond.

1078
01:22:52,386 --> 01:22:54,888
I just wanted to keep hearing it.

1079
01:22:57,391 --> 01:22:59,935
That was two weeks after we met.

1080
01:23:02,104 --> 01:23:05,899
It only took her two weeks
to fall in love with me before.

1081
01:23:16,952 --> 01:23:18,745
She doesn't love me.

1082
01:24:10,881 --> 01:24:12,633
Sign here, please.

1083
01:24:49,169 --> 01:24:51,171
Come here, little buddy.

1084
01:25:00,013 --> 01:25:01,181
Diane?

1085
01:25:02,224 --> 01:25:03,350
Hey.

1086
01:25:04,059 --> 01:25:06,228
- How are you?
- Listen...

1087
01:25:08,855 --> 01:25:11,108
I know it's been years.

1088
01:25:11,191 --> 01:25:13,694
I was away for a while.

1089
01:25:14,361 --> 01:25:17,114
I never had a chance to apologize.

1090
01:25:18,031 --> 01:25:20,867
I was just going through
a really weird time,

1091
01:25:21,034 --> 01:25:23,870
but your dad ended it

1092
01:25:25,414 --> 01:25:28,000
as soon as your mother
confronted him about us.

1093
01:25:28,083 --> 01:25:31,044
And I just always wanted 
you to know that.

1094
01:25:31,545 --> 01:25:34,089
I don't mean to open old wounds, but...

1095
01:25:34,214 --> 01:25:37,968
I just really needed 
to say that I'm sorry.

1096
01:25:39,553 --> 01:25:42,139
No, I'm really glad that 
you said something.

1097
01:25:42,222 --> 01:25:44,933
You were always a really good friend.

1098
01:25:45,100 --> 01:25:47,728
I just wish I could've returned the favor.

1099
01:25:48,103 --> 01:25:51,773
The lilies were bad,
so I got sunflowers instead.

1100
01:26:02,576 --> 01:26:04,995
- I wanted to tell you.
- You knew?

1101
01:26:06,288 --> 01:26:08,248
You knew the whole time?

1102
01:26:09,750 --> 01:26:11,585
- I'm sorry.
- Don't talk to me.

1103
01:26:11,668 --> 01:26:14,629
Paige. Paige. Paige!

1104
01:26:18,175 --> 01:26:20,427
Hey, where have you 
been all day, stranger?

1105
01:26:22,763 --> 01:26:23,972
Paige?

1106
01:26:26,099 --> 01:26:27,809
I ran into Diane Chain at the store.

1107
01:26:30,437 --> 01:26:33,857
That's why I left, isn't it?
Because I found out.

1108
01:26:35,859 --> 01:26:39,196
Mom, I barely even know who I am,

1109
01:26:39,279 --> 01:26:41,656
and then it turns out you're lying to me,

1110
01:26:41,782 --> 01:26:45,202
and you've used my accident
to rewrite the past?

1111
01:26:47,204 --> 01:26:49,831
I couldn't bear the thought
of losing you again.

1112
01:26:50,791 --> 01:26:54,419
Do you have any idea how 
betrayed I feel right now?

1113
01:26:54,503 --> 01:26:56,505
I'm sorry, Paige.

1114
01:26:56,630 --> 01:26:58,840
We were happier than 
we'd been in years.

1115
01:26:58,965 --> 01:27:01,802
- Mom!
- We finally had you back again.

1116
01:27:01,885 --> 01:27:04,388
- Back on your terms!
- No!

1117
01:27:04,471 --> 01:27:06,640
- Yes, as usual!
- Paige!

1118
01:27:06,723 --> 01:27:09,851
He cheated on you with my friend!

1119
01:27:11,019 --> 01:27:13,313
How could you stay with him?

1120
01:27:14,648 --> 01:27:15,816
I...

1121
01:27:18,360 --> 01:27:20,487
I was going to leave.

1122
01:27:22,739 --> 01:27:24,825
I was. I was all ready to leave.

1123
01:27:25,492 --> 01:27:29,830
And then one afternoon,
I was all alone in the house,

1124
01:27:30,831 --> 01:27:35,377
and I started looking at
all the photographs of you

1125
01:27:36,086 --> 01:27:37,712
and your...

1126
01:27:39,840 --> 01:27:41,675
And your sister.

1127
01:27:42,342 --> 01:27:46,847
And the house seemed 
so full of all of us.

1128
01:27:49,057 --> 01:27:51,268
We were a family, Paige.

1129
01:27:52,853 --> 01:27:55,522
And I realized in that moment that

1130
01:27:56,231 --> 01:27:59,860
that was the most important 
thing in the world for me.

1131
01:28:00,277 --> 01:28:03,113
And I couldn't, I couldn't,

1132
01:28:03,864 --> 01:28:06,408
I could not go.

1133
01:28:08,869 --> 01:28:11,079
So, you just wasped it away?

1134
01:28:11,580 --> 01:28:12,706
No.

1135
01:28:13,623 --> 01:28:17,043
I chose to stay with him

1136
01:28:18,211 --> 01:28:21,381
for all the things that he had done right

1137
01:28:23,049 --> 01:28:27,053
and not to leave him for the
one thing that he had done wrong.

1138
01:28:30,557 --> 01:28:32,559
I chose to forgive him.

1139
01:28:38,440 --> 01:28:40,317
Maybe Leo was right.

1140
01:28:41,485 --> 01:28:46,072
Maybe I can't figure out who 
I am and be around all of you.

1141
01:29:00,795 --> 01:29:02,923
I still feel a little chilly.
I don't care what you say.

1142
01:29:04,508 --> 01:29:05,967
That's fine.

1143
01:29:08,345 --> 01:29:09,429
Paige.

1144
01:29:17,354 --> 01:29:19,773
- I'm sorry.
- ls everything okay?

1145
01:29:23,109 --> 01:29:26,196
Look, you two obviously 
need to talk, so I'm just...

1146
01:29:26,279 --> 01:29:27,781
- Okay.
- Talk to you later.

1147
01:29:27,864 --> 01:29:29,491
All right, bye.

1148
01:29:32,118 --> 01:29:33,870
I'm... I'm sorry.

1149
01:29:35,830 --> 01:29:37,457
What happened?

1150
01:29:40,001 --> 01:29:42,546
- Can I ask you something?
- Yeah.

1151
01:29:43,630 --> 01:29:45,966
You can always ask me anything.

1152
01:29:46,633 --> 01:29:49,302
Did you know about my dad's affair?

1153
01:29:50,637 --> 01:29:51,805
Yeah.

1154
01:29:52,472 --> 01:29:53,807
I knew.

1155
01:30:00,146 --> 01:30:01,815
Why didn't you tell me?

1156
01:30:09,072 --> 01:30:12,534
There were so many 
times that I almost did.

1157
01:30:15,203 --> 01:30:18,331
But to drive you away
from your family again?

1158
01:30:19,040 --> 01:30:20,667
That just felt wrong.

1159
01:30:22,752 --> 01:30:24,629
I wanted your love, I...

1160
01:30:24,713 --> 01:30:26,548
Just not like that.

1161
01:30:27,841 --> 01:30:29,676
I wanted to earn it.

1162
01:30:45,567 --> 01:30:49,195
I just don't think I can afford
to lose them right now.

1163
01:30:52,032 --> 01:30:53,450
So don't.

1164
01:31:01,458 --> 01:31:04,836
Certain parties have sought
to nullify various congressional acts,

1165
01:31:04,919 --> 01:31:07,756
claiming that repeated extensions
of copyright protection

1166
01:31:07,881 --> 01:31:09,966
constitute a perpetual copyright

1167
01:31:10,050 --> 01:31:14,054
of the sort the drafters of the 
Constitution would have rejected.

1168
01:31:14,137 --> 01:31:18,892
The United States Supreme Court,
in the 2003 case of Eldred v. Ashcroft...

1169
01:31:26,566 --> 01:31:27,942
Thanks for lunch.

1170
01:31:28,068 --> 01:31:31,613
Actually, there's something
that I wanted to tell you.

1171
01:31:31,738 --> 01:31:32,906
Okay.

1172
01:31:33,782 --> 01:31:36,242
Things are over with Rose.

1173
01:31:37,452 --> 01:31:39,245
I ended it, Paige.

1174
01:31:40,080 --> 01:31:42,832
No. Why did you do that?

1175
01:31:42,916 --> 01:31:44,709
I thought you were getting engaged...

1176
01:31:44,793 --> 01:31:46,378
We were, but that was before you.

1177
01:31:46,461 --> 01:31:47,921
No, that was after me.

1178
01:31:48,004 --> 01:31:50,173
Okay, it was after you,
but it was before this you.

1179
01:31:50,256 --> 01:31:52,133
It was before the old you came back.

1180
01:31:54,135 --> 01:31:56,304
Jeremy, I'm not the old me.

1181
01:31:57,430 --> 01:31:59,015
I'm just me.

1182
01:31:59,474 --> 01:32:02,686
I'm just the me that's 
trying to figure it out still.

1183
01:32:03,103 --> 01:32:07,941
I understand, but, whichever it is,
the old you or the new you, I don't care.

1184
01:32:09,609 --> 01:32:12,070
I know you remember what we 
were like together. I know you do.

1185
01:32:12,153 --> 01:32:15,281
- This is our chance to get that back.
- What we had was wonderful.

1186
01:32:15,365 --> 01:32:17,909
Those were wonderful memories,
but those were...

1187
01:32:17,992 --> 01:32:20,078
Those are my only memories.

1188
01:32:20,161 --> 01:32:22,539
Everything after you is erased.

1189
01:32:23,456 --> 01:32:24,666
I...

1190
01:32:26,501 --> 01:32:31,715
I have to discover what it's like
to be without you, on my own.

1191
01:32:34,217 --> 01:32:37,137
Are you sure you don't remember
breaking up with me the first time?

1192
01:32:37,971 --> 01:32:39,389
Why?

1193
01:32:39,472 --> 01:32:41,808
'Cause it sounded a 
hell of a lot like that.

1194
01:32:46,062 --> 01:32:47,480
Let's go.

1195
01:32:58,199 --> 01:33:00,952
Hey. I was looking all over.

1196
01:33:01,035 --> 01:33:04,914
I was worried when I didn't 
see you outside the library.

1197
01:33:07,500 --> 01:33:08,752
So...

1198
01:33:11,546 --> 01:33:14,758
How's that intellectual 
property class going?

1199
01:33:20,346 --> 01:33:23,224
Actually, I wanna talk to you about that.

1200
01:33:23,933 --> 01:33:26,895
I've decided to leave law school.

1201
01:33:28,855 --> 01:33:31,024
And I'm gonna get an 
apartment in the city.

1202
01:33:31,900 --> 01:33:34,402
It's happening all over again, isn't it?

1203
01:33:34,527 --> 01:33:36,196
Damn it, Paige.

1204
01:33:37,697 --> 01:33:39,240
I've made a lot of mistakes.

1205
01:33:40,033 --> 01:33:44,245
Dad, this isn't about you
or anything you've done.

1206
01:33:44,871 --> 01:33:49,125
This is about me, 
who I want to be, who I am.

1207
01:33:50,376 --> 01:33:55,048
Just tell me what to say,
so I don't lose you again.

1208
01:33:58,384 --> 01:33:59,969
You won't.

1209
01:34:08,061 --> 01:34:10,230
A moment of impact.

1210
01:34:16,277 --> 01:34:20,573
A moment of impact
whose potential for change

1211
01:34:20,657 --> 01:34:24,118
has ripple effects far beyond 
what we can predict,

1212
01:34:27,330 --> 01:34:30,250
sending some particles 
crashing together

1213
01:34:32,418 --> 01:34:34,754
making them closer than before,

1214
01:34:41,261 --> 01:34:44,514
while sending others spinning 
off into great ventures

1215
01:34:47,433 --> 01:34:50,687
landing where you never 
thought you'd find them.

1216
01:34:54,274 --> 01:34:57,652
You see, that's the thing
about moments like these.

1217
01:34:58,528 --> 01:35:00,196
You can't,

1218
01:35:01,030 --> 01:35:03,283
no matter how hard you try,

1219
01:35:04,033 --> 01:35:06,786
control how they're gonna affect you.

1220
01:35:08,621 --> 01:35:12,292
You just gotta let the colliding 
particles land where they may

1221
01:35:13,293 --> 01:35:17,380
and wait until the next collision.

1222
01:35:25,305 --> 01:35:28,266
I vow to help you love life,

1223
01:35:28,349 --> 01:35:30,727
to always hold you with tenderness,

1224
01:35:30,810 --> 01:35:33,688
and to have the patience 
that love demands.

1225
01:35:33,813 --> 01:35:35,899
To speak when words are needed

1226
01:35:35,982 --> 01:35:38,651
and to share the silence when they're not.

1227
01:35:38,735 --> 01:35:42,322
To agree to disagree on red velvet cake.

1228
01:35:42,989 --> 01:35:47,368
And to live within the warmth of 
your heart and always call it home.

1229
01:36:33,289 --> 01:36:34,374
Hi.

1230
01:36:37,377 --> 01:36:38,753
Hi.

1231
01:36:42,215 --> 01:36:45,426
I hope you didn't come all the way
into the city for hot chocolate.

1232
01:36:45,551 --> 01:36:49,222
Actually, I moved back
here six months ago.

